verbs.description: enrank (third-person singular simple present enranks, present participle enranking, simple past and past participle enranked)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To place in ranks or in order.
examples: When I had againe forgiuen them, behold, they laid vpon me a new crime, which themselues had wrought, and signed with their owne hands; and shortly after were enranked in battell against me in the field  […]

entries.meaning: (figurative, obsolete) To classify (someone in a particular group); to enroll, register.
examples: […]  thy Lord or Maister enranks thee with the deceaved sort, and so forgets thee!
